snippet.textDisplay: I myself lost my father 6 years ago when I was 10. I lost him 8 months after he was diagnosed with 2 types of cancers, a rare type of leukaemia and lung cancer. These 8 months were the best and the worst of my life because I lost my father and when I wake up I remember all over again that he is dead and cancer took him away from me. On the 9th December 2013 my mother woke me up and told me that he died in the hospital and I cried all the tears I had in me I screamed  until my lungs nearly collapsed, I wanted to wake up from this horrible dream but it was the reality. Every day I wake up with the fear of losing someone I love and mostly my mom because she is the only one I have left and with the fear of having cancer as well. But this year for me didn't  start well because nearly a month ago I was diagnosed  with lupus and I didn't know how to react to it because I was happy I didn't have cancer but at the same time I was scared because it was a mystery to me I didn't know if I would get to love to one day because I may die from a kidney , lung or heart failure and it's  the worst thing to know that you may die tomorrow or in a week. I'm someone that does have many friends because I'm scared that one day I get attached and loose them too. I have 3 friends and they are all that I could hope for . Always remember to cherish the ones you love and live like there is no tomorrow.

snippet.textDisplay: Xavier you were such a great, strong and living soul. You’ve been fighting for so long and you’re setting a big example to so many people right here. It breaks my heart that you’re not with us anymore but i know that you’re in a good place now and that you’re looking down on everyone and telling everyone to keep fighting. You’re an angel and i never thought i would feel like this about a person that i never personally have met. But dear Xavier you opened my heart. And i had so many bad days and so many bad weeks you just made me realize that I shouldn’t give up now and that i still have time. I wish your family all the best and i send them all my love. Dear Yes Theory Team, you guys are amazing and you’ve made his last few month’s to great memories. Thank you for being like that, for being human, and for being such good role models on this platform. I wish i could hug you all right now. And for everyone reading this, if you’re going through something remember Xavier and remember to keep on fighting because you’re worth it and you are loved. And if you haven’t heard it yet, i love you and you deserve to be here. Don’t give up!

snippet.textDisplay:
Just watched this and it made me cry.... Matt and everyone involved with this have accomplished such a grand feat, which is befriending someone and giving him care, warm affection, and loving memories right at a time when he probably thought he wouldn't have the chance or time to experience any of that again.


To do that for a human being is to plant the seed of good in the world. That is to truly create connection, unity, brotherhood, empathy...


Matt, I hope you do realize you have given this guy and his family the last biggest memory of his lifetime, and for that you should be proud of yourself. When the curtains close, the video ends, and the views are gone, all that's left is how you make people feel.


And you gave him something to make him feel good again, even for a short while.


You'll be in his heart forever, and he'll be in yours as well.


Thanks for this beautiful example of what humanity is all about, and what our true calling is.

snippet.textDisplay:
I know a lot of people have many religions and disagree with each other and are highly sensitive to this talk. But when people think death is the end, it's not. I am a christian, and I believe death is the end of this small world, but the start of something greater. When people give their lives to Jesus they are then in the hands of God and even death can't take them from his hands. When they die they go meet the Father in heaven. And no you won't grow wings and become an angel and sing forever. We all sin in this world, and once your body dies your soul lives on forever with the being that created the amazing person that you are. And this is the proof: "For God so loved the world that he gave his one and only Son, that whoever believes in him shall not perish but have eternal life" -john 3:16. A lot of people throw this around, but it's so real man.

Yes theory is doing something truly wonderful, but if they did all this in the name of Jesus. Imagine the lives that would change even more, imagine how real being a follower of God would be. And it's not about sitting in a church listening to some guy talk for hours. It's real, it's about facing fears, walking through life with those you love. And all the while God is behind you guiding your steps. I'm not sure why I felt like I needed to share this. But I hope it brought some comfort to you. God bless all of you, stay strong, keep fighting. You all are amazing❤️

snippet.textDisplay: This is so heart warming and eye opening to watch. I couldn’t help but cry through almost the whole video. I had a friend who passed away from brain cancer when we were 15 years old. She had been told countless amounts of times that she only had x amount of days to live, but she always pushed through. She even had fought the cancer away...or that’s what the doctors thought at least...but unfortunately it came back unexpectedly and even then she still lived a month longer than they expected her to. I witnessed first hand someone fighting every minute of everyday and she was the happiest person I knew despite the terrible condition she was in. Truly touching to be close with someone who has such a passion and determination for life, truly nothing like it. He will always be with you
